  "prompt": "Is there a database of retail grocery prices?",
  "response": "There are several sources for retail grocery price data:\n\n1. Government Sources:\n- USDA Agricultural Marketing Service\n- Bureau of Labor Statistics Consumer Price Index\n- State-level agriculture departments\n\n2. Commercial Databases:\n- IRI (Information Resources Inc.)\n- Nielsen\n- Numerator\n- SPINS (for natural/organic products)\n\n3. Online Price Comparison Websites:\n- Basket.com\n- Grocery.com\n- Some offer regional pricing data\n\n4. Academic/Research Resources:\n- Some universities maintain regional price databases\n- USDA Economic Research Service\n\n5. Crowdsourced Options:\n- Numbeo.com (user-submitted prices)\n- Some local community websites\n\nMost comprehensive databases are subscription-based and can be expensive. Government and academic sources often provide free aggregate data, but may not have real-time or detailed pricing.\n\nThe best source depends on your specific needs (national vs. regional, type of data, frequency of updates, etc.).\n\nWould you like more details about any of these sources?",
